pril 26. That spring, one Hooker physician career began as another ended before it could start."},{"number":2,"category":"death","header":"Septicemia claimed the best-known Cambridge physician","body":"Edward Dwight Hooker graduated Harvard College in 1880 and Harvard Medical School in 1884, trained at New York State Hospital, and became one of the best-known physicians in Cambridge and Arlington. He died of septicemia October 27, 1911 at age fifty-two, continuing the Hooker family's Harvard medical tradition into a third generation."},{"number":3,"category":"legacy","header":"Three generations of Harvard physicians: 1822, 1855, 1884","body":"His grandfather Dr. Anson Hooker took his Harvard Medical degree in 1822, his father Dr. Anson Parker Hooker earned a Harvard A.B. in 1851 and returned for his M.D. in 1855, and Edward Dwight completed the arc with a Harvard A.B. in 1880 and M.D. in 1884 — three consecutive Hooker physicians trained at Harvard across sixty-two years. Each carried the Cambridge practice to the next generation."}],"quotes":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"burial":{"cemetery_id":"CEM549"},"residence":{},"sources":[{"short":"Edward Hooker 1909","page":"Entry 2762"}],"research_sources":[],"slug":"edward-hooker-1858"},"HD4942":{"id":"HD4942","is_placeholder":false,"has_descendants_documented":false,"former_ids":[],"bio":{"display_name":"Rebecca Hooker Flint","first_name":"Rebecca","middle_name":"Hooker","last_name":"Flint","maiden_name":"Hooker","married_names":["Flint"]},"gender":"female","birth":{"year":1908,"city":"Cambridge","county":"Middlesex","state":"Massachusetts","country":"United States"},"death":{"year":1990,"country":"United States"},"baptism":{},"classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_thomas_spouse":false,"is_talcott_spouse":false,"generation_from_thomas":9,"include_in_path_calculation":true,"descent_paths_to_thomas":1,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":true,"is_progenitor":false,"is_easter_eg